---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import StickyNav from "../components/StickyNav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";

const phone = "tel:+14077343968";
const phoneDisplay = "407-734-3968";
---

<Layout
  title="Repiping in Avalon Park | Whole-Home Pipe Replacement | Bonet Plumbing"
  description="Repiping services in Avalon Park, FL 32828. CPVC replacement, whole-home repiping & pipe upgrades across every village. Licensed plumber. Call 407-734-3968."
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: "Home", url: "https://bonetplumbing.com/" },
    { name: "Service Areas", url: "https://bonetplumbing.com/#service-areas" },
    { name: "Avalon Park Plumber", url: "https://bonetplumbing.com/avalon-park-plumber" },
    { name: "Repiping in Avalon Park" }
  ]}
>
  <StickyNav />
  <main>
    <section class="bg-gradient-to-b from-primary/[0.03] via-white to-white py-16 md:py-24">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-text leading-tight mb-4">
          Repiping in Avalon Park
        </h1>
        <div class="w-16 h-1 bg-accent rounded-full mb-6"></div>
        <p class="text-lg text-text-secondary mb-4 max-w-2xl">
          Avalon Park homes were built starting in 2003, and many used CPVC plumbing that's now 15-20+ years old. Central Florida's hard water, high temperatures, and chlorine levels in the municipal water supply break down CPVC over time — making it brittle and prone to cracking without warning.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-text-secondary mb-8 max-w-2xl">
          If you're dealing with frequent leaks, discolored water, or low water pressure in your Avalon Park home, it may be time for a repipe. We replace aging CPVC and other failing pipe materials with modern, durable plumbing across every village in the 32828 zip code.
        </p>

        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3 mb-10">
          <a href={phone} class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-3 bg-accent hover:bg-accent-light text-white font-bold text-lg px-8 py-4 rounded-lg shadow-md transition-all duration-200 hover:shadow-lg">
            <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M2.25 6.75c0 8.284 6.716 15 15 15h2.25a2.25 2.25 0 002.25-2.25v-1.372c0-.516-.351-.966-.852-1.091l-4.423-1.106c-.44-.11-.902.055-1.173.417l-.97 1.293c-.282.376-.769.542-1.21.38a12.035 12.035 0 01-7.143-7.143c-.162-.441.004-.928.38-1.21l1.293-.97c.363-.271.527-.734.417-1.173L6.963 3.102a1.125 1.125 0 00-1.091-.852H4.5A2.25 2.25 0 002.25 4.5v2.25z"/>
            </svg>
            Call Now: {phoneDisplay}
          </a>
          <a href="/#contact" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 bg-primary hover:bg-primary-light text-white font-bold text-lg px-8 py-4 rounded-lg shadow-md transition-all duration-200 hover:shadow-lg">
            Get a Free Estimate
          </a>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-text mb-6">Repiping Services We Provide</h2>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-12">
          <div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-xl p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-text mb-3">Whole-Home Repiping</h3>
            <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">Complete replacement of all supply lines in your home with modern PEX or copper piping. We minimize wall damage, work efficiently to keep your home livable during the job, and restore water same-day when possible.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-xl p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-text mb-3">CPVC Replacement</h3>
            <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">CPVC becomes brittle after 15-20 years in Florida's conditions. If your Avalon Park home has CPVC supply lines that are cracking, we replace them with PEX — a flexible, durable material that won't degrade from heat or chlorine.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-xl p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-text mb-3">Partial Repiping</h3>
            <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">Sometimes only part of your plumbing is failing — a specific section of pipe or one bathroom's supply lines. We can replace just the affected areas if the rest of your plumbing is in good shape.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-surface border border-border rounded-xl p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-text mb-3">Pipe Inspections</h3>
            <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">Not sure if you need a repipe? We'll inspect your plumbing system and give you an honest assessment — including how much life your current pipes have left and whether repair or replacement makes more sense.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Warning Signs -->
        <div class="bg-primary/5 border border-primary/10 rounded-xl p-6 mb-10">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-text mb-3">Signs Your Avalon Park Home Needs Repiping</h2>
          <ul class="space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-primary shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 9v3.75m-9.303 3.376c-.866 1.5.217 3.374 1.948 3.374h14.71c1.73 0 2.813-1.874 1.948-3.374L13.949 3.378c-.866-1.5-3.032-1.5-3.898 0L2.697 16.126z M12 15.75h.007v.008H12v-.008z"/></svg>
              <span class="text-text-secondary text-sm"><strong>Frequent pinhole leaks</strong> — if you've repaired multiple leaks in different spots, the whole system is likely degrading, not just the spots you've patched</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-primary shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 9v3.75m-9.303 3.376c-.866 1.5.217 3.374 1.948 3.374h14.71c1.73 0 2.813-1.874 1.948-3.374L13.949 3.378c-.866-1.5-3.032-1.5-3.898 0L2.697 16.126z M12 15.75h.007v.008H12v-.008z"/></svg>
              <span class="text-text-secondary text-sm"><strong>Rusty or discolored water</strong> — brown or yellow water coming from your taps means corrosion is happening inside your pipes</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-primary shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 9v3.75m-9.303 3.376c-.866 1.5.217 3.374 1.948 3.374h14.71c1.73 0 2.813-1.874 1.948-3.374L13.949 3.378c-.866-1.5-3.032-1.5-3.898 0L2.697 16.126z M12 15.75h.007v.008H12v-.008z"/></svg>
              <span class="text-text-secondary text-sm"><strong>Low water pressure throughout the house</strong> — mineral buildup and pipe deterioration narrow the inside of your pipes, reducing flow to every fixture</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-primary shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 9v3.75m-9.303 3.376c-.866 1.5.217 3.374 1.948 3.374h14.71c1.73 0 2.813-1.874 1.948-3.374L13.949 3.378c-.866-1.5-3.032-1.5-3.898 0L2.697 16.126z M12 15.75h.007v.008H12v-.008z"/></svg>
              <span class="text-text-secondary text-sm"><strong>CPVC pipes over 15 years old</strong> — many Avalon Park homes in the earliest-built villages have CPVC supply lines that are now entering their failure window</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-accent/10 border border-accent/20 rounded-lg p-6 mb-10">
          <p class="font-bold text-text mb-1">Save 15% on Repiping</p>
          <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm">Mention this offer when you call. Available for Avalon Park residents in the 32828 zip code.</p>
          <p class="text-text-secondary text-xs mt-2">Florida License #CFC1434246 · Licensed & Insured</p>
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
          <a href={phone} class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-3 bg-accent hover:bg-accent-light text-white font-bold text-lg px-8 py-4 rounded-lg shadow-md transition-all duration-200 hover:shadow-lg">
            Call Now: {phoneDisplay}
          </a>
          <a href="/#contact" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 bg-primary hover:bg-primary-light text-white font-bold text-lg px-8 py-4 rounded-lg shadow-md transition-all duration-200 hover:shadow-lg">
            Get a Free Estimate
          </a>
        </div>

        <!-- FAQ Section -->
        <div class="mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-border">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text mb-6">Repiping FAQs — Avalon Park</h2>
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-text mb-2">Does my Avalon Park home have CPVC pipes?</h3>
              <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">Most Avalon Park homes built between 2003 and 2012 used CPVC for supply lines. You can check by looking at exposed pipes in your garage, under sinks, or near the water heater — CPVC is a light yellow or cream-colored plastic pipe. If you're not sure, we can inspect and tell you exactly what you have.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-text mb-2">How long does a whole-home repipe take?</h3>
              <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">Most Avalon Park homes can be repiped in 1-2 days depending on the size and layout. We restore water service as quickly as possible so you're not without water for long. Drywall patching and paint touch-up may take an additional day.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-text mb-2">What material do you replace pipes with?</h3>
              <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">We typically install PEX (cross-linked polyethylene) piping, which is flexible, resistant to scale buildup and chlorine, and lasts 40-50+ years. It's the industry standard for residential repiping in Florida and handles our water conditions far better than CPVC.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-bold text-text mb-2">Is repiping worth the cost, or should I just keep repairing leaks?</h3>
              <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">If you've had more than 2-3 leaks in different locations, the pipe material itself is failing — not just one bad joint. Each repair is a temporary fix on a system that's deteriorating. Repiping solves the problem permanently, protects your home from water damage, and is often required by insurance companies after repeated claims.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Cross Navigation -->
        <nav class="mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-border" aria-label="Related services and areas">
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
            <div>
              <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-text mb-4">Other Services in Avalon Park</h2>
              <ul class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
                <li><a href="/drain-cleaning-avalon-park" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-light font-medium text-sm transition-colors">Drain Cleaning</a></li>
                <li><a href="/water-heater-services-avalon-park" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-light font-medium text-sm transition-colors">Water Heater Services</a></li>
                <li><a href="/emergency-plumber-avalon-park" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-light font-medium text-sm transition-colors">Emergency Plumber</a></li>
                <li><a href="/avalon-park-plumber" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-light font-medium text-sm transition-colors">All Avalon Park Services</a></li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-text mb-4">Nearby Service Areas</h2>
              <ul class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
                <li><a href="/waterford-lakes-plumber" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-light font-medium text-sm transition-colors">Waterford Lakes</a></li>
                <li><a href="/alafaya-plumber" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-light font-medium text-sm transition-colors">Alafaya</a></li>
                <li><a href="/east-orlando-plumber" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-light font-medium text-sm transition-colors">East Orlando</a></li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </nav>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <!-- FAQPage Schema -->
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Does my Avalon Park home have CPVC pipes?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Most Avalon Park homes built between 2003 and 2012 used CPVC for supply lines. You can check by looking at exposed pipes in your garage, under sinks, or near the water heater — CPVC is a light yellow or cream-colored plastic pipe. If you're not sure, we can inspect and tell you exactly what you have."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How long does a whole-home repipe take?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Most Avalon Park homes can be repiped in 1-2 days depending on the size and layout. We restore water service as quickly as possible so you're not without water for long. Drywall patching and paint touch-up may take an additional day."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What material do you replace pipes with?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "We typically install PEX (cross-linked polyethylene) piping, which is flexible, resistant to scale buildup and chlorine, and lasts 40-50+ years. It's the industry standard for residential repiping in Florida and handles our water conditions far better than CPVC."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is repiping worth the cost, or should I just keep repairing leaks?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "If you've had more than 2-3 leaks in different locations, the pipe material itself is failing — not just one bad joint. Each repair is a temporary fix on a system that's deteriorating. Repiping solves the problem permanently, protects your home from water damage, and is often required by insurance companies after repeated claims."
